# Documentation skills

When creating or editing project documentation, **read and follow the matching skill first** — do not improvise structure from memory or copy legacy README prose.

## Routing

| Target | Skill |
|--------|-------|
| Any `README.md` **except** `docs/README.md` | **readme-generation** |
| `docs/**/*.md` (including `docs/README.md`) | **reference-docs** |

## All READMEs matter

This monorepo has multiple READMEs; each is a real publish or discovery surface:

| README | Audience / surface |
|--------|-------------------|
| [`README.md`][root-readme] | **GitHub** — workspace overview, clone, local dev |
| [`src/core/dhara_storage/README.md`][crate-dhara-storage] | **crates.io** (`readme` in Cargo.toml) |
| [`src/core/dhara_storage_dal/README.md`][crate-dal] | **crates.io** |
| [`src/bindings/dharastorage-ffi/README.md`][crate-dharastorage] | **crates.io** (`readme` in Cargo.toml) |
| [`tooling/dhara_tool/README.md`][crate-tool] | **crates.io** |
| [`src/bindings/csharp/Dhara.Storage/README.md`][nuget-readme] | **NuGet** (`PackageReadmeFile` / `dhara.config.toml`) |

When editing a project README, **scope content to that package** — install, API, and examples for that crate or NuGet package only. Link to the root README or `docs/` for workspace-wide context; do not paste the whole monorepo story into every package README.

When editing the **root** README, orient GitHub visitors: what the workspace is, how to build/verify, and where each published package lives.

**Exception:** `tooling/dhara_tool/package/README.md` is internal operator notes for builder assets (excluded from `cargo package`), not a registry README — keep it short; use **reference-docs** tone, not the 8-section layout.

## Must do

- Discover facts from **that project's** manifest (`Cargo.toml`, `.csproj`, `dhara.config.toml`), code, and workflows before writing.
- Use **reference-style** markdown links in README and docs.
- Link to `docs/` for depth instead of duplicating ABI, pipeline, or architecture essays in any README.

## Must not

- Put agent prompts, Cursor rules, or skill instructions in any README.
- Assume only the repo-root README exists or matters.
- Treat existing README structure as canonical when it conflicts with readme-generation (recreate from code if needed).

## New reference docs

- Filename: `docs/<topic>.md` (kebab-case).
- Optional assets: `docs/references/`.
- Update [docs/README.md][docs-index] when adding a top-level doc.

